tematic and rescue excavations of the physical remains of the wall as it evolved over eleven centuries and through more than a dozen construction phases. It reviews issues relating to structure, chronology and topography of the ancient city wall, as well as to the management of its remains by the state authorities. The enormous amount of primary evidence makes the book essential reading for scholars of the topography of ancient Athens. This monograph also aspires to increase community awareness of cultural heritage in everyday urban contexts, as the wall has been preserved in a number of ways: in basements of buildings, reburied in situ, in the open air or beneath glass floors.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aCity wallszGreecezAthensxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zGreecezAthens. 0aFortificationzGreecezAthensxHistoryyTo 1500. 7aART / History / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aDefense.  aExcavations.  aPreservation.  aTopography.1 aPitt, Robert K.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019 Englishz978311061009308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019z9783110605945oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831106370690 cprintz978311063321440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311063820240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110638202423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110638202.jpg  a978-3-11-061009-3  EBOOK